  <!-- SESSION B3 -->
  <div class="session-header" id="session-b3">
    <span class="session-label">Part B — Session 3</span>
    <h3>Academic Interests, Practical Priorities &amp; Full Synthesis</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="coach-note"><strong>Coach Note:</strong> Session 3 is the most critical conversation. Begin with a two-minute recap of Sessions 1 and 2 before presenting new results.</div>
  <div class="quote-block" style="margin-top:16px;">"Before we look at today's results, let's revisit where we've landed. Does the Holland code still feel right? Has the VIA result shifted how you think about what you want from a program?"</div>

  <div class="framework">
    <span class="framework-number">Framework 4</span>
    <h4>Academic Interest Inventory</h4>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Framework Purpose</span>
      <p>Maps pure intellectual curiosity to field clusters, independent of job market pressure or perceived ability. Genuine interest is one of the strongest predictors of academic persistence and completion.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Holland Alignment</span>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>What It Means</th><th>How to Debrief</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Holland and Academic Interest align</td><td>High confidence. Both frameworks independently confirm the same cluster.</td><td>Name the convergence explicitly. Use it to anchor all program recommendations.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Holland and Academic Interest diverge</td><td>Often reveals external pressure or an unexplored interdisciplinary option.</td><td>Probe which result feels more genuinely their own. Explore bridging programs.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Validation Prompt</span>
      <div class="quote-block">"Looking at this ranking — is that your genuine passion, or what you feel pressure to be interested in?"</div>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Coaching Prompts</span>
      <ul class="prompt-list">
        <li>"What is the last thing you read, watched, or looked up purely because it interested you — with no assignment attached?"</li>
        <li>"If you could study anything for a year with no grades, no degree requirement, and no job market pressure, what would you study?"</li>
        <li>"Is there a gap between what interests you most and what you think you're supposed to study? Where does that pressure come from?"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Coach Notes — Academic Interests</span>
      <div style="min-height:80px;border:1px dashed rgba(212,160,23,0.2);padding:12px;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="framework">
    <span class="framework-number">Framework 5</span>
    <h4>Practical Priorities</h4>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Framework Purpose</span>
      <p>Surfaces the real-world constraints that determine which paths are actually viable. The results page applies a GPA-based filter to program suggestions — reference this explicitly. For students below program minimums, identify bridge options: community college transfer paths, grade improvement plans, or open-access programs that feed into target programs.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Validation Prompt</span>
      <div class="quote-block">"Do these answers reflect your actual situation — or were some of them based on what you wish were true?"</div>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Coaching Prompts</span>
      <ul class="prompt-list">
        <li>"Given the financial profile we're working with, which program types are realistically on the table and which aren't?"</li>
        <li>"Is the income goal driven by genuine need — or by comparison to others? Would a lower starting salary in the right field actually be acceptable?"</li>
        <li>"Are there constraints here that feel fixed but might actually be flexible — with family, an employer, or a financial aid office?"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="coach-note">
      <strong>Coach Note:</strong> The most common practical blocker is a fixed belief about financial constraints that has never been tested. Before ruling out any path on cost grounds, always ask: "Have you actually researched scholarships, grants, and aid for this specific program?" The answer is almost always no.
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <span class="block-label">Coach Notes — Practical Priorities</span>
      <div style="min-height:80px;border:1px dashed rgba(212,160,23,0.2);padding:12px;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <span class="block-label">Full Education Path Planner Synthesis</span>
    <p>After all five frameworks, identify cross-framework convergence. Program recommendations with the strongest evidence are those supported by three or more frameworks pointing in the same direction.</p>
    <ul class="watch-list" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <li>Does the top Academic Interest cluster align with the Holland code? Alignment = high confidence. Divergence = explore why.</li>
      <li>Does the VARK result eliminate any program formats on the shortlist? Remove those programs before proceeding.</li>
      <li>Does the VIA signature strength align with the campus culture of the top programs?</li>
      <li>Do the Practical Priorities constraints accommodate the top program directions?</li>
      <li>Does the Career Destination Vision from intake align with what these programs produce?</li>
    </ul>
    <table class="synthesis-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Theme / Pattern</th><th>Frameworks Supporting It</th><th>Confidence Level</th><th>Direction to Explore</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="min-height:40px;"></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="min-height:40px;"></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <span class="block-label">Program Shortlist</span>
    <p style="font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:8px;">After synthesis, list the 2–3 programs that survive all five framework filters.</p>
    <table class="ref-table">
